OL,3,CScientists observe Mounjaro slashing
OL,4,Cfood cravings by suppressing brain
OL,5,Csignals
OL,7,FThey found episodes of intense food
OL,8,Fpreoccupation and cravings were linked
OL,9,Fto low-frequency brain signals, known
OL,10,Fas delta-theta activity, in the
OL,11,Fnucleus accumbens, a part of the
OL,12,Fbrain's reward system.
OL,14,FIn two patients, electrical
OL,15,Fstimulation to areas of the brain
OL,16,Freduced this signal.
OL,18,FThe third patient was given Mounjaro
OL,19,Fto manage diabetes following weight-
OL,20,Floss surgery, which also resulted in
OL,21,Freductions in food cravings.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
